  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7115 sitting just above the massive +12.2B gamma wall at 7100, dealers are actively selling into this strength to hedge their long gamma positions. The PIN regime and heavy positive gamma concentration between 7050-7200 creates a strong magnetic pull toward the 7100 strike, with dealers providing natural resistance on any further upside attempts. Key levels to watch are the 7100 support (where dealer selling pressure peaks) and 7150 resistance wall, with the 6872 flip strike acting as the lower boundary where dealer behavior would shift to accelerating any breakdown.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pulled back toward 7100 with limited upside past 7150.",
